1. To connect the server aremotely from another server and write something in /tmp 

    sshpass -p "<Password>" ssh ec2-user<IP-Address> -C "echo Hello >> /tmp/hello.txt"

    -C --> Argument 

2. To install mySql in a server from another server remotely

    sshpass -p "<Password>" ssh ec2-user<IP-Address> -C "curl https://raw.githubusercontent.com/aws-devopsprocloud/shell-script/refs/heads/main/08-install-mysql.sh | sudo bash"


